 them to upgrade all their items to class III effects or suffer without those effects.  A virtual downgrade in power if you consider that these items are being added to increase caster power.<br><br>Secondly, the effects apparently don't scale in power, they only increase the level of spells that they will effect.  So if I had a class II effect and hit 49, to gain the same benefits I had before I'd be forced to upgrade my equip.  That just doesn't make sense, upgrade my equipment to stay on the same power curve.<br><br>It just doesn't seem right that I would arbitrarily be forced to outgrow my gear.  Some of it might be hard to upgrade and will be used for a long time, yet will have lost its focus benefit long before.  <br><br>As an analogy, you don't see the damage bonus on weapons decrease as you level up, it increases.  Why should the bonus on caster armor decrease as you level up?  The percent doesn't technically decrease, but if it stops working for you that's the same thing.<br><br><br>This isn't a rant, it's just feedback that I had no idea where else to post. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/udygaroftest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dygar of Test</A> at: 6/4/02 2:42:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uozmandias.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ozmandias</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(6/4/02 2:53:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/feqtestregistryfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=549.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/bigmaxxx/skelstretch.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus effects (no spoilers)</span><hr size=1> I'd love to find 