 you guessed it above, just live with it and upgrade your gear every 20 levels as opposed to every 5-10 a melee has to.  Oh, and I almost forgot, comparing weapons and armor is like comparing apples and oranges.  Comparing the scalability of Melee armor to the scalability of Caster armor is a better idea.  Like I mentioned above Melee's have always had to upgrade or suffer, and I believe that it should have been the same for casters since day 1.  And before you dismiss my arguements as that of a Melee who knows nothing about caster items, my first character was a Wizard, so I do know how caster items have scaled in the past.  After I got my mid level gear with my wizard I stopped rolling in randoms because I really didn't need to upgrade my gear anymore, I had 255 int at level 45, the only possible reason I would have to upgrade equipment was +mana items or if I wanted to be a smartass +AC items. <p>________________________________________________________<BR><a href><font color=#CC90FF><i><b>"I am a Child of the Universe.  With a glitter of my life I travel through black, velvet space, and the gates of time.  I am a star awoken from it's sleep - by the longing cries of mankind's dreams.  Dreams of harmony, love, and a Child of the Universe."</b></i></font></a><BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=165032"><img border="0" src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jwebb2/Serenity.jpg" width="109" height="230"></a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=164717"><img border="0" src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jwebb2/Pickett.jpg" width="89" height="230"></a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=165042"><img border="0" src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jwebb2/Aphroditex.jpg" width="110" height="230"></a><BR>Click on a character to see their profile.<BR><a href><font face="Monotype Corsiva" color="#FF7000" size=4><b>Member of Anlah'shok</