b?topicID=549.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus effects (no spoilers)</span><hr size=1> I really hate when people post &quot;stop your bitching!  We've been suffering, so now you need to too&quot; posts.  Typically they just make me want to rant, but I'm not going to waste the time.<br><br>Bottom line is, the focus items need to be tweeked.  Impskin Gloves, a rare drop from a 26th level rare spawn in SolA have Affliction Efficiency I.  Sounds great, but a group who is able to get these gloves is going to have absolutely no use for the focus effect on them.  To put it in a language a melee can understand, it's like killing a 26th level mob and getting a breastplate with a recommended level of 51.  Sure, you can use it, but you don't the full effect from it.<br><br>There are many other examples of focus effects that don't make sense for the level of critter that drops them.  Grey Flesh gloves drop from a 51st level mob.  They have amazing stats, so I'm damn happy about having them, but the Focus effect (Affliction Efficiency II) is useless since by the time i could hunt this beast I was casting 49th+ level dots.  (on a side note, I never managed to get a pair myself.  Luckily, I know some of the nicest people ever who hooked me up).  <br><br>I agree with Dygar in that the effects should just be upgrades of previous effects.  Affliction Efficiency I could be a 15% reduction of mana, 20% for II, and 25% for III.  It would match up against melee equivilents much better then, IMHO. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/uaphroditex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aphroditex</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(6/10/02 6:02:18 pm)</font>